    "RepaymentStatus": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Repayment Instruction Status: The coded value that reflects the stage or outcome of a repayment instruction in the loan lifecycle.\r\n\r\nTypical Status Values\r\nPending → Instruction created but not yet executed.\r\nScheduled → Instruction queued for a future due date.\r\nExecuted → Repayment successfully processed and settled.\r\nPartially Executed → Only part of the repayment amount applied (common in partial payments).\r\nFailed/Rejected → Instruction could not be processed (e.g., insufficient funds, mandate failure).\r\nCancelled → Instruction withdrawn before execution.\r\nReversed → Instruction executed but later reversed (e.g., dispute, error correction).\r\nRestructured → Instruction modified due to loan restructuring.",
      "x-status": "stable",
      "x-modified-by": null,
